DESCRIPTION:
------------
Minesweeper CLI is a console-based version of the classic Minesweeper
game. It features an 8×8 board, three difficulty levels, automatic
mine placement after the first move, recursive revealing of empty
tiles, scoring, and a persistent high‑score system.

The goal is to reveal all safe tiles without triggering a mine.

FEATURES:
--------
• Three difficulty levels:
    - Easy (10 mines)
    - Medium (15 mines)
    - Expert (20 mines)
• 8×8 game board
• First move is always safe (mines placed afterward)
• Recursive reveal of empty tiles
• ANSI-colored board display
• High‑score saving with sorting and trimming to top 7 entries
• Score based on difficulty level
• About section with author information

CONTROLS:
---------
• Enter coordinates as:
      xy   (e.g., 11, 38)
  or  x y  (e.g., 1 1, 3 8)

• x = column (1–8)
• y = row    (1–8)

Tile types:
• Hidden tile:   #
• Mine:          *
• Empty tile:    (blank)
• Number tiles:  1–9 (colored)

GAME RULES:
-----------
• Your first move is always safe.
• Mines are placed only after the first reveal.
• Numbers indicate how many mines are in the 8 surrounding tiles.
• Revealing a mine ends the game immediately.
• You win when the number of hidden tiles equals the number of mines.

SCORING:
--------
Points per revealed tile:
• Easy:   +1 point
• Medium: +2 points
• Expert: +3 points

High‑score system:
• Scores are saved to:
      %USERPROFILE%\.polsoft\hi-score\Minesweeper.txt
• Entries include:
      SCORE | NAME | LEVEL
• Sorted descending
• Only the top 7 results are kept

MENUS:
------
Main Menu:
