  [2] High Scores
  [3] About
  [4] Exit

Difficulty Menu:
  [1] Easy
  [2] Medium
  [3] Expert

ABOUT SECTION:
--------------
Displays:
• Author name
• Email
• GitHub link
• Game description
• Controls
• Scoring rules

REQUIREMENTS:
-------------
• Windows 7 / 10 / 11
• Standard CMD environment
• ANSI support (Windows 10+)
• Console size: 85×30 (set automatically)

USAGE:
------
Run:

  minesweeper.cmd

Then:
  • Choose difficulty
  • Enter coordinates to reveal tiles
  • Continue until you win or hit a mine

After game over:
  • Enter your name for the scoreboard
  • Results are saved automatically
  • You return to the main menu

NOTES:
------
• There is no flagging system — gameplay focuses on fast revealing.
• The board resets completely for each new game.
• Invalid inputs are ignored safely.

END:
----
When the game ends, the program displays:

  [ WIN ] Congratulations!
or
  [ BOOM ] Loss!

Your score is then recorded.

